eer2016\">{{cite web|title=2018 U.S. Gazetteer Files|url=https://www2.census.gov/geo/docs/maps-data/data/gazetteer/2018_Gazetteer/2018_gaz_place_02.txt|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=Jul 1, 2019}}</ref>\n|area_magnitude           = \n|area_total_km2           = 4.53\n|area_land_km2            = 3.22\n|area_water_km2           = 1.31\n|area_total_sq_mi         = 1.75\n|area_land_sq_mi          = 1.24\n|area_water_sq_mi         = 0.51\n\n<!-- Population -->\n|population_as_of         = [[2010 United States Census|2010]]\n|population_footnotes     = \n|population_total         = 282\n|population_density_km2   = 96.51\n|population_density_sq_mi = 250.00\n|timezone                 = [[Alaska Time Zone|Alaska (AKST)]]\n|utc_offset               = -9\n|timezone_DST             = AKDT\n|utc_offset_DST           = -8\n|elevation_footnotes      = \n|elevation_m              = 8\n|elevation_ft             = 26\n|coordinates              = {{coord|61|30|49|N|160|21|33|W|region:US-AK|display=inline}}\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]\n|postal_code              = 99626\n|area_code                = [[Area code 907|907]]\n|area_code_type           = [[North American Numbering Plan|Area code]]\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = 02-45460\n|blank1_name              = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank1_info              = {{GNIS 4|1405763}}\n|website                  = \n|footnotes                = \n|pop_est_as_of = 2018\n|pop_est_footnotes = <ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\"/>\n|population_est = 311\n|unit_pref = Imperial\n}}\n'''Lower Kalskag''' ({{lang-esu|Qalqaq}}) is a city in [[Bethel Census Area, Alaska|Bethel Census Area]], [[Alaska]], [[United States]]. It is twenty-six miles west of [[Aniak, Alaska|Aniak]]. At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] the population was 282, up from 267 in 2000.\n\n==Geography==\nLower Kalskag is located at {{coord|61|30|49|N|160|21|33|W|type:city}} (61.513735, -160.359050).<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geographies/reference-files/time-series/geo/gazetteer-files.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2011-04-23|date=2011-02-12|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the city has a total area of {{convert|1.7|sqmi|km2}}, of which, {{convert|1.3|sqmi|km2}} of it is land and {{convert|0.4|sqmi|km2}} of it (25.58%) is water.\n\nLower Kalskag, referred to by the locals as just \"Lower\", is linked to [[Upper Kalskag, Alaska|Upper Kalskag]] (Upper) by a single two mile maintained gravel/dirt road.\n\nLower Kalskag is accessible only by small plane, boat, and vehicles via the river \"ice road\" (Winter only).\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1940= 76\n|1950= 88\n|1960= 122\n|1970= 183\n|1980= 246\n|1990= 291\n|2000= 267\n|2010= 282\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=311\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=June 4, 2019}}</ref>\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name=\"DecennialCensus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\nLower Kalskag first appeared on the 1940 U.S. Census erroneously<ref>http://edu.georgetowntc.com/our-courses/nuna-land/upper-kalskag-2/historical-information-page.html#previous-photo</ref> as the unincorporated village of Kalskag. In 1950, it reported as Lower Kalskag. It formally incorporated in 1969.\n\nAs of the [[census]]<ref name=\"GR2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 267 people, 66 households, and 54 families residing in the city.  The [[population density]] was 208.2 people per square mile (80.5/km\u00b2).  There were 79 housing units at an average density of 61.6 per square&nbsp;mile (23.8/km\u00b2).  The racial makeup of the city was 4.49% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 88.76% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], and 6.74% from two or more races.\n\nThere were 66 households out of which 62.1% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 47.0% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 24.2% had a female householder with no husband present, and 16.7% were non-families. 15.2% of all households were made up of individuals and 1.5% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 4.05 and the average family size was 4.53.\n\nIn the city, the population was spread out with 44.9% under the age of 18, 13.5% from 18 to 24, 22.1% from 25 to 44, 15.4% from 45 to 64, and 4.1% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 21 years. For every 100 females, there were 96.3 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 98.6 males.\n\nThe [[median income]] for a household in the city was $25,625, and the median income for a family was $27,500. Males had a median income of $16,667 versus $36,250 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $7,654.  About 36.7% of families and 40.6% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 51.4% of those under the age of eighteen and 35.7% of those sixty five or over.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Coord|display=title|61.513735|-160.35905}}\n{{Bethel Census Area, Alaska}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities in Bethel Census Area, Alaska]]\n[[Category:Cities in Alaska]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|official_name            = Lower Kalskag, Alaska\n|native_name              = Qalqaq\n|settlement_type          = [[City (Alaska)|City]]\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    = <!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = StSeraphimChurch.jpg\n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = The historic [[St. Seraphim Chapel]]\n|image_flag               = \n|image_seal               = <!-- Maps -->\n|pushpin_map  = USA Alaska\n|pushpin_map_caption  = Location in Alaska\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = [[United States]]\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1        = [[Alaska]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of boroughs and census areas in Alaska|Census Area]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Bethel Census Area, Alaska|Bethel]]\n|government_footnotes     = \n|government_type          = \n|leader_title             = [[Mayor]]\n|leader_name              = Crim Evan<ref>{{Cite book|title=2015 Alaska Municipal Officials Directory|location=Juneau|publisher=Alaska Municipal League|year=2015|page=98}}</ref>\n|leader_title1            = [[Alaska Senate|State senator]]\n|leader_name1             = [[Lyman Hoffman]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|D]])\n|leader_title2            = [[Alaska House of Representatives|State rep.]]\n|leader_name2             = [[Tiffany Zulkosky]] (R)\n|established_title        = [[Municipal corporation|Incorporated]]\n|established_date         = 1969<ref>{{cite book|title=1996 Alaska Municipal Officials Directory|location=[[Juneau]]|publisher=Alaska Municipal League/[[Alaska Department of Commerce, Community and Economic Development|Alaska Department of Community and Regional Affairs]]|date=January 1996|page=92}}</ref>\n\n<!-- Area -->\n|area_footnotes           = <ref name=\"CenPopGazetteer2016\">{{cite web|title=2018 U.S. Gazetteer Files|url=https://www2.census.gov/geo/docs/maps-data/data/gazetteer/2018_Gazetteer/2018_gaz_place_02.txt|publisher=United States Census Bureau|accessdate=Jul 1, 2019}}</ref>\n|area_magnitude           = \n|area_total_km2           = 4.53\n|area_land_km2            = 3.22\n|area_water_km2           = 1.31\n|area_total_sq_mi         = 1.75\n|area_land_sq_mi          = 1.24\n|area_water_sq_mi         = 0.51\n\n<!-- Population -->\n|population_as_of         = [[2010 United States Census|2010]]\n|population_footnotes     = \n|population_total         = 282\n|population_density_km2   = 96.51\n|population_density_sq_mi = 250.00\n|timezone                 = [[Alaska Time Zone|Alaska (AKST)]]\n|utc_offset               = -9\n|timezone_DST             = AKDT\n|utc_offset_DST           = -8\n|elevation_footnotes      = \n|elevation_m              = 8\n|elevation_ft             = 26\n|coordinates              = {{coord|61|30|49|N|160|21|33|W|region:US-AK|display=inline}}\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]\n|postal_code              = 99626\n|area_code                = [[Area code 907|907]]\n|area_code_type           = [[North American Numbering Plan|Area code]]\n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               = 02-45460\n|blank1_name              = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank1_info              = {{GNIS 4|1405763}}\n|website                  = \n|footnotes                = \n|pop_est_as_of = 2018\n|pop_est_footnotes = <ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\"/>\n|population_est = 311\n|unit_pref = Imperial\n}}\n'''Lower Kalskag''' (''Qalqaq'' in [[Central Alaskan Yup'ik language|Central Alaskan Yup'ik]]) is a city in [[Bethel Census Area, Alaska|Bethel Census Area]], [[Alaska]], [[United States]]. It is twenty-six miles west of [[Aniak, Alaska|Aniak]]. At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]] the population was 282, up from 267 in 2000.\n\n==Geography==\nLower Kalskag is located at {{coord|61|30|49|N|160|21|33|W|type:city}} (61.513735, -160.359050).<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geographies/reference-files/time-series/geo/gazetteer-files.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2011-04-23|date=2011-02-12|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref>\n\nAccording to the [[United States Census Bureau]], the city has a total area of {{convert|1.7|sqmi|km2}}, of which, {{convert|1.3|sqmi|km2}} of it is land and {{convert|0.4|sqmi|km2}} of it (25.58%) is water.\n\nLower Kalskag, referred to by the locals as just \"Lower\", is linked to [[Upper Kalskag, Alaska|Upper Kalskag]] (Upper) by a single two mile maintained gravel/dirt road.\n\nLower Kalskag is accessible only by small plane, boat, and vehicles via the river \"ice road\" (Winter only).\n\n==Demographics==\n{{US Census population\n|1940= 76\n|1950= 88\n|1960= 122\n|1970= 183\n|1980= 246\n|1990= 291\n|2000= 267\n|2010= 282\n|estyear=2018\n|estimate=311\n|estref=<ref name=\"USCensusEst2018\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/popest/data/tables.2018.html|title=Population and Housing Unit Estimates|accessdate=June 4, 2019}}</ref>\n|footnote=U.S. Decennial Census<ref name=\"DecennialCensus\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/programs-surveys/decennial-census.html|title=Census of Population and Housing|publisher=Census.gov|accessdate=June 4, 2015}}</ref>\n}}\nLower Kalskag first appeared on the 1940 U.S. Census erroneously<ref>http://edu.georgetowntc.com/our-courses/nuna-land/upper-kalskag-2/historical-information-page.html#previous-photo</ref> as the unincorporated village of Kalskag. In 1950, it reported as Lower Kalskag. It formally incorporated in 1969.\n\nAs of the [[census]]<ref name=\"GR2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2008-01-31|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 267 people, 66 households, and 54 families residing in the city.  The [[population density]] was 208.2 people per square mile (80.5/km\u00b2).  There were 79 housing units at an average density of 61.6 per square&nbsp;mile (23.8/km\u00b2).  The racial makeup of the city was 4.49% [[Race (United States Census)|White]], 88.76% [[Race (United States Census)|Native American]], and 6.74% from two or more races.\n\nThere were 66 households out of which 62.1% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 47.0% were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, 24.2% had a female householder with no husband present, and 16.7% were non-families. 15.2% of all households were made up of individuals and 1.5% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.  The average household size was 4.05 and the average family size was 4.53.\n\nIn the city, the population was spread out with 44.9% under the age of 18, 13.5% from 18 to 24, 22.1% from 25 to 44, 15.4% from 45 to 64, and 4.1% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 21 years. For every 100 females, there were 96.3 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 98.6 males.\n\nThe [[median income]] for a household in the city was $25,625, and the median income for a family was $27,500. Males had a median income of $16,667 versus $36,250 for females. The [[per capita income]] for the city was $7,654.  About 36.7% of families and 40.6% of the population were below the [[poverty line]], including 51.4% of those under the age of eighteen and 35.7% of those sixty five or over.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Coord|display=title|61.513735|-160.35905}}\n{{Bethel Census Area, Alaska}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Cities in Bethel Census Area, Alaska]]\n[[Category:Cities in Alaska]]\n", "name_user": "Menchi", "label": "safe", "comment": "langtags", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lower_Kalskag,_Alaska"}
